Shane Lowry surged up the leaderboard at the RBC Heritage after carding 65 to sit just one stroke off the pace ahead of the final round. The Irishman mixed eight birdies with bogeys on the par-four third and sixth holes, while Harold Varner III went bogey-free with the day’s best score of 63 to be 11 under at Hilton Head Island. Joining Lowry in second spot at 10 under were South African Erik van Rooyen and second-round leader Patrick Cantlay, after respective rounds of 67 and 70. Lowry’s fellow Irishman Graeme McDowell was part of a group tied for 30th at five under. England’s Tommy Fleetwood carded an impressive 64 to be at eight under, his countryman Ian Poulter was another stroke back. The British contingent at Harbour Town Golf Links in South Carolina was completed by Tyrrell Hatton at three under and Luke Donald another five strokes back. Collated third round scores and totals (USA unless stated, Irish in bold, Par 71) 202 Harold Varner III 67 72 63 203 Patrick Cantlay 66 67 70, Shane Lowry (Irl) 66 72 65, Erik van Rooyen (Rsa) 69 67 67 204 Matt Kuchar 68 69 67, Sepp Straka (Aut) 66 71 67, Hudson Swafford 69 69 66, Aaron Wise 68 68 68 205 Joel Dahmen 69 67 69, Tommy Fleetwood (Eng) 71 70 64, Billy Horschel 69 69 67, Jordan Spieth 69 68 68 206 Corey Conners (Can) 66 72 68, Maverick McNealy 71 70 65, Joaquin Niemann (Chi) 65 72 69, Guillermo Mito Pereira (Chi) 66 71 69, Ian Poulter (Eng) 71 68 67, Robert Streb 68 67 71, Adam Svensson (Can) 66 73 67, Cameron Tringale 69 67 70, Cameron Young 63 73 70 207 Wyndham Clark 68 73 66, Lucas Glover 68 71 68, Sung Jae Im (Kor) 70 70 67, Peter Malnati 69 73 65, Troy Merritt 69 70 68, Kevin Na 70 69 68, Matthew NeSmith 70 68 69, Alexander Noren (Swe) 70 70 67 208 Adam Hadwin (Can) 69 69 70, Patton Kizzire 67 71 70, Jason Kokrak 70 68 70, Graeme McDowell (Irl) 66 76 66, Scott Piercy 67 72 69, J. T. Poston 68 72 68, Chad Ramey 67 70 71, Brendon Todd 72 68 68 209 Daniel Berger 71 70 68, Cameron Davis (Aus) 69 73 67, Dylan Frittelli (Rsa) 70 71 68, Doug Ghim 70 72 67, Branden Grace (Rsa) 71 70 68, Bill Haas 67 74 68, Adam Long 69 73 67, Ben Martin 71 70 68, Collin Morikawa 70 70 69, Danny Willett (Eng) 70 72 67 210 Tyler Duncan 68 73 69, Brian Gay 67 75 68, Brian Harman 72 70 68, Tyrrell Hatton (Eng) 67 72 71, Jim Herman 69 71 70, Si Woo Kim (Kor) 69 70 71, Pat Perez 68 73 69, Doc Redman 69 71 70 211 Anirban Lahiri (Ind) 69 73 69, Chengtsung Pan (Tai) 70 70 71, Charl Schwartzel (Rsa) 68 72 71, Webb Simpson 69 73 69, Roger Sloan (Can) 68 71 72, Sahith Theegala 71 70 70, Justin Thomas 70 71 70 212 Denny McCarthy 67 75 70, Camilo Villegas (Col) 71 67 74, Matthias Schwab (Aut) 67 74 71 213 Stewart Cink 67 75 71 214 Henrik Stenson (Swe) 71 71 72 215 Luke Donald (Eng) 70 69 76 216 Joseph Bramlett 69 73 74 217 Brian Stuard 73 69 75 220 Jonathan Byrd 68 74 78